<br>
A new policy at DAZ is what they call the &quot;Platinum membership&quot;.  This allows an artist to spend $99 a year and to download their highest end assets for only $1.99 each.  This aspect of membership is, to me, wonderful.  Also, on many other items in the store, the PM gets a discounted rate.  This, too, is wonderful.  Those who are not members don't get the discount rates, which is understandable to me.  The real flame here is the straw that broke this camel's back.<br>
<br>
If you are not a Platinum member and pay them $99 a year, you now have NO ACCESS to many high end items AT ALL!  It's their company, but in my view the, &quot;give us $99 or get bent!&quot; message is horribly offensive.  To me, it's damn near extortion.  Never mind my years of loyalty.  Never mind that over half the models I have now and I paid full price for are also on the Platinum list (I could have saved hundreds of dollars).  Now they want me to pay $99 just to download them?  What if I only find a single $35 model this year that I can use, since my needs are specialized?  Doesn't that mean my &quot;discounted rate&quot; for that model is $134?  If I don't find one this year, will they refund my $99?<br>
<br>
DAZ could have (and should have) stopped at the option for giving discounts to Platinum members, but they chose to penalize everyone else.  Because of this stance, I have chosen to boycott DAZ and look for a competitor.  This saddens me to do, since I enjoyed my professional relationship with them so much.  They are fantastic artists, but they lack a decent level of respect.  Fact is, they made artwork I liked to buy... and they paid their bills because I liked to buy them.  Now they will need to find someone else to push around.<br>
<br>
Safeway (club card), QFC Food Centers (QFC Card), Albertson's (Preferred Membership Card ... baby, it's your store now... not mine!), DAZ3D (Platinum Membership)<br>
<br>
See all of you stores later... nice work, marketing department!<br>
